description: From Middle English lustful, from Old English lustfull (“desirous, wishful”); equivalent to lust +‎ -ful. Cognate with Dutch lustvol (“lustful, lusty”), German lustvoll (“pleasurable”), Swedish lustfyllt (“pleasurable”), Swedish lustfyllda (“lustful”).

adjectives.description: lustful (comparative more lustful, superlative most lustful)

entries.meaning: Full of lust; driven by lust.
